ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Astro 565 synthesizes topics from all across astronomy into a coherent history of the universe and the ways in which we make these inferences. I would recommend this class to an experienced graduate student: I felt it was more effective for them because they had a much more complete background of knowledge to knit together.
I would certainly recommend this class to other students.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I do not think I will apply these concepts to my own research, but it helped me gain a better understanding of the whole of astronomy.
This class is a great intro to the concepts and literature of the field of galaxy evolution.
